    "body": "### Problem\n\nClosing nvim by closing conhost window causes error and freezes nvim window. I think the specific issue is that SIGHUP causes slow shutdown.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4bc7d4ac-dabf-4a1d-938e-3728e6bda4f9\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Open conhost\n2. Run nvim.exe --clean\n3. Close conhost window\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNvim closes instantly without a message like `:!qa`. This is how vim works.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, vim 9.1.1335\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 11 24H2\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nconhsot (latest pre-installed)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nN/A (windows)\n\n### Installation\n\nwinget install neovim",
